The collapse of Bernard L. Madoff's company came just hours before his arrest Thursday on a single securities fraud count.
Madoff, a former chairman of Nasdaq stock market, was arrested Thursday in New York hours after the collapse of Bernard L. Madoff Investment Securities LLC.
Bramdean Alternatives invested around 21 million pounds (23.3 million euros, 31.2 million dollars), or around 9.5 percent of its portfolio, with Madoff's company, Bernard L. Madoff Investment Securities LLC.
